SIMPLE: tilt
RECORDS: 5

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tilt
<hw>Tilt</hw> <pr>(t⟦icr⟧lt)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>telt</ets> (perhaps from the Danish), <ets>teld</ets>, AS.
<ets>teld</ets>, ge<ets>teld</ets>; akin to OD. <ets>telde</ets>, G.
<ets>zelt</ets>, Icel. <ets>tjald</ets>, Sw. <ets>t⟦aum⟧lt</ets>,
<ets>tj⟦aum⟧ll</ets>, Dan. <ets>telt</ets>, and AS. be<ets>teldan</ets>
to cover.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A covering overhead; especially, a
tent.</def> <rj><au>Denham.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The cloth covering of a cart or a wagon.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Naut.)</fld> <def>A cloth cover of a boat; a small
canopy or awning extended over the sternsheets of a boat.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Tilt boat</b></col> <fld>(Naut.)</fld>, <cd>a boat
covered with canvas or other cloth.</cd> -- <col><b>Tilt roof</b></col>
<fld>(Arch.)</fld>, <cd>a round-headed roof, like the canopy of a
wagon.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tilt</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Tilt
<hw>Tilt</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Tilted</conjf>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Tilting</conjf>.]</vmorph> <def>To cover with a tilt, or
awning.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tilt</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Tilt
<hw>Tilt</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[OE. <ets>tilten</ets>,
<ets>tulten</ets>, to totter, fall, AS. <ets>tealt</ets> unstable,
precarious; akin to <ets>tealtrian</ets> to totter, to vacillate, D.
<ets>tel</ets> amble, ambling pace, G. <ets>zelt</ets>, Icel.
<ets>t⟦oum⟧lt</ets> an ambling pace, <ets>t⟦oum⟧lta</ets> to amble. Cf.
<er>Totter</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To incline; to tip; to raise
one end of for discharging liquor; <as>as, to <ex>tilt</ex> a
barrel</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To point or thrust, as a lance.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Sons against fathers <qex>tilt</qex> the fatal lance.</q>
<rj><qau>J. Philips.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To point or thrust a weapon at.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Beau. & Fl.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>To hammer or forge with a tilt hammer; <as>as, to
<ex>tilt</ex> steel in order to render it more ductile</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tilt</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 4 ====
HEADWORD: Tilt
<hw>Tilt</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To run or ride, and
thrust with a lance; to practice the military game or exercise of
thrusting with a lance, as a combatant on horseback; to joust; also,
figuratively, to engage in any combat or movement resembling that of
horsemen tilting with lances.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He <qex>tilts</qex>⟦br⟧
With piercing steel at bold Mercutio's breast.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Swords out, and <qex>tilting</qex> one at other's breast.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>But in this tournament can no man <qex>tilt</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Tennyson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The fleet, swift <qex>tilting</qex>, o'er the surges flew.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To lean; to fall partly over; to tip.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The trunk of the body is kept from <qex>tilting</qex> forward by
the muscles of the back.</q> <rj><qau>Grew.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tilt</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 5 ====
HEADWORD: Tilt
<hw>Tilt</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A thrust, as
with a lance.</def> <rj><au>Addison.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A military exercise on horseback, in which the
combatants attacked each other with lances; a tournament.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>See <er>Tilt hammer</er>, in the
Vocabulary.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Inclination forward; <as>as, the <ex>tilt</ex> of a
cask</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Full tilt</b></col>, <cd>with full force.</cd>
<rj><au>Dampier.</au></rj></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tilter</ent>⟦br⟧
